  description="The 7-letter bingo words formed entirely from common Scrabble tiles (S, E, A, R, T, I, N, O, L, D). High-frequency bingos you'll see in almost every game."
  keywords="common tile bingos scrabble, easy 7 letter words, high frequency bingos, satine words, common scrabble bingos, beginner bingo words, frequent tile combinations"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Seven-Letter Words with Common Tiles — Easy Bingos You'll Draw Often",
    "description": "The 7-letter bingo words formed entirely from common Scrabble tiles (S, E, A, R, T, I, N, O, L, D). High-frequency bingos you'll see in almost every game.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-15",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/seven-letter-words-with-common-tiles" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the most common tiles in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "The 10 most common tiles in a standard Scrabble set are E (12 tiles), A (9), I (9), O (8), N (6), R (6), T (6), L (4), S (4), and D (4). These 10 letters account for 68 of the 98 letter tiles in the bag — nearly 70% of all draws." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Why are common-tile bingos easier to achieve?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Since common tiles make up roughly 70% of the bag, you draw them far more often than rare letters. A bingo that uses only common tiles (like RETINAS or SARDINE) requires no rare draws — every letter in the word is one you'll see multiple times per game. This makes these bingos statistically much more likely to appear on your rack." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best stem for common-tile bingos?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "SATINE (S, A, T, I, N, E) is the most productive stem for common-tile bingos. Every letter in SATINE is a high-frequency 1-point tile, meaning you draw this combination often. It pairs with over 20 different seventh letters to form valid 7-letter words including NASTIER (+R), DETAINS (+D), and ELASTIN (+L)." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <a href="/blog/bingos/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors text-gray-300">Bingos</a>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Seven-Letter Words with Common Tiles — Easy Bingos You'll Draw Often</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-15">June 15, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>6 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Not all bingos are created equal. Some require rare tiles like Q, X, or Z — letters you might draw once per game. Others are built entirely from the tiles you'll see on almost every turn. These common-tile bingos are the ones worth memorising first, because you'll actually get the chance to play them.</p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Common = Frequent</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">COMMON TILES = COMMON BINGOS</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">10 letters that make up 70% of your draws</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The letters <span class="text-white font-mono font-bold">E A I O N R T L S D</span> dominate the tile bag. Bingos formed entirely from these tiles appear on your rack far more often than any others — learn them first and you'll score 50-point bonuses in nearly every game.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">What Makes a Tile "Common"?</h2>
      <p>In a standard 100-tile Scrabble set, frequency varies wildly. E appears 12 times while Q, X, and Z appear just once each. The tiles that dominate your draws are the ones with 4+ copies in the bag — and they're all worth just 1-2 points each.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">E ×12</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Most frequent</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">A ×9</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">I ×9</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">O ×8</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">3rd tier</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">N,R,T ×6</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Each</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">L,S,D ×4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Each</p></div>
        </div>
