      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Grouped by Stem Family</h2>
      <p>Common-tile bingos cluster around a few productive stems. Learning the stem gives you access to all its offspring words — far more efficient than memorising bingos one by one.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧬 SATINE Family (A E I N S T)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NASTIER, ANTSIER, DETAINS, INSTEAD, STAINED, ELASTIN, SALIENT — the most fertile stem produces the most common-tile bingos.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧬 RETINA Family (A E I N R T)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">RETINAS, TRAINED, DETRAIN — adding S, D, or L to RETINA yields high-probability bingos using only common tiles.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧬 SALINE Family (A E I L N S)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">NAILERS, ALINERS, SALTIER, REALIST — the L inclusion opens up a different set of bingo endings.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
          <p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🧬 ORNATE Family (A E N O R T)</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">SENATOR, TREASON — the O-vowel stem that produces recognisable words most players already know.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Overlap Advantage</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Notice how many letters these stems share: <span class="text-white font-medium">A, E, I, N</span> appear in all four. If you hold these four letters, you're already two-thirds of the way to multiple different stems. Any 3 tiles from {"{"} S, T, R, L, O, D {"}"} completes one.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">How to Prioritise Your Study</h2>
      <p>With dozens of possible common-tile bingos, where should a learner start? Prioritise by how often the rack combination actually appears:</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-purple-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">🧩 Study Priority Order</p>
        <div class="space-y-3">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">1</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">SATINE + one common consonant</span> — Start with NASTIER, DETAINS, ELASTIN. The stem uses only 1-point tiles you'll draw constantly.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">2</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">RETINA + S or D</span> — RETINAS and TRAINED are everyday words you'll recognise instantly when they appear on your rack.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">3</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">SALINE + R or T</span> — NAILERS and SALIENT add L to the mix. L appears 4 times in the bag, so it's a reliable draw.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="shrink-0 w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-purple-900/50 border border-purple-500/40 flex items-center justify-center text-xs text-purple-300 font-bold">4</span>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-white font-medium">ORNATE + S</span> — SENATOR and TREASON are words even non-Scrabble players recognise. Easy to spot, easy to play.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

