      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Holding Common Tiles for Bingo Potential</h2>
      <p>The best part about common-tile bingos: you don't need luck to draw toward them. Smart rack management almost guarantees you'll hold a productive combination within a few turns.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ Keep This</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Rack: SATINE + V → Play V in a short word. Keep SATINE intact. Next draw has a 70% chance of being another common tile that completes a bingo.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ Avoid This</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Rack: SATINE + V → Play INVEST for 12 points. You broke a perfect stem for a mediocre score. Now you need to rebuild from scratch.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">The 70% rule:</span> With common tiles making up 70% of the bag, your next draw after keeping a common-tile stem is overwhelmingly likely to be another common tile. The probability compounds in your favour.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Dump high-point singles:</span> Tiles like Q, Z, X, and J are worth points but terrible for bingo potential. If you're building toward a common-tile bingo, play these expensive tiles in short words first.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Multiple stems = multiple chances:</span> If your rack has AEINT, you're partially building SATINE, RETINA, and ENTAIL simultaneously. Any of several draws completes one of them.</p>
        </div>
